    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        ALLISON 2000 SERIES&#8482; (LCT) TRANSMISSION ELECTRONIC CONTROLS - DESCRIPTION - SHIFT LEVER SELECTOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT LEVER SELECTOR</title>
        <para>To move the shift lever (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0824703">Figure 3</hotlnk>) between "R," "N," and "D," a lockout must be disengaged by
            using the thumb release (detent unlock button) on the shifter handle. All other ranges can be selected by
            moving the lever without using the thumb release.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0824703" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0824703.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="152px" resolution="100"/>
            <caption>Shift Lever Selector</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DETENT UNLOCK BUTTON</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ECONOMY MODE SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RANGE INHIBIT LIGHT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The shift lever display illumination is controlled by the dash panel light control.</para>
    </svcproc>
